# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Appendix: structure-analysis toolkit -- radial distribution functions
#
# Compute g(r) of bcc iron (Mendelev EAM) at three temperatures: room temperature, an
# intermediate temperature, and above the superheating limit, where the
# crystal melts during the run and the final sampling sees the liquid.
# A force-less pair_style zero is overlaid only to extend the neighbor
# list to 8.5 A so that g(r) covers several coordination shells
# independent of the force cutoff.  Outputs rdf_fe_<T>.dat; plot all
# materials with rdf-plot.py.

variable T index 300 1100 2400

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

lattice bcc 2.8553
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 2.8553 2.8553 2.8553
region box block 0 10 0 10 0 10
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (28.553 28.553 28.553)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 2000 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (28.553 28.553 28.553)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.000 seconds
mass 1 55.845
pair_style hybrid/overlay eam/fs zero 8.5
pair_coeff * * eam/fs Fe_mm.eam.fs Fe
Reading eam/fs potential file Fe_mm.eam.fs with DATE: 2007-06-11
pair_coeff * * zero

velocity all create $(2.0*v_T) 31415 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
velocity all create 600 31415 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
fix md all npt temp ${T} ${T} 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
fix md all npt temp 300 ${T} 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
fix md all npt temp 300 300 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
thermo 1000
thermo_style custom step temp pe press vol
run 10000
Neighbor list info ...
  update: every = 1 steps, delay = 0 steps, check = yes
  max neighbors/atom: 2000, page size: 100000
  master list distance cutoff = 10.5
  ghost atom cutoff = 10.5
  binsize = 5.25, bins = 6 6 6
  2 neighbor lists, perpetual/occasional/extra = 2 0 0
  (1) pair eam/fs, perpetual
      attributes: half, newton on
      pair build: half/bin/atomonly/newton
      stencil: half/bin/3d
      bin: standard
  (2) pair zero, perpetual
      attributes: half, newton on, cut 10.5
      pair build: half/bin/atomonly/newton
      stencil: half/bin/3d
      bin: standard
